    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Laced boots or shoes with the vamp and tongue cut in one piece and the eyelet tabs stitched on top of the vamp; introduced in the early 19th century. Boot versions often have straight side seams and originally no back seam.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
